  "texts": [
    "The authors adopted a new strategy, which implements a semantic procedure for calculating the similarity between users, based on a measure of the semantic similarity between the products they have rated, aiming to enhance flexibility in similarity detection and reduce the sparsity of CF.",
    "By using the hierarchical structure of an ontology, the strategy intelligently categorizes products and determines their similarity based on how close they are to the hierarchy and how many common ancestors they have.",
    "This structure also helps to choose the best level of abstraction needed to form neighborhoods.Tarus et al. [13] proposed a hybrid knowledge-based recommendation approach, which integrates ontology and sequential learning patterns for recommending learning resources to learners.",
    "Ontology encapsulates knowledge about learners and resources, while a sequential pattern mining algorithm is applied to discover the learner's historical sequential learning patterns.",
    "Collaborative filtering is employed to compute similarities of ratings and make predictions for a target learner."
  ],
